<br>
The other problem is that you can only have one macro running at a time, so once you kick off mend, you won't be able to use any other macros you may have until it comes back.<br>
<br>
I use a method similar to Kurrlee's, and it works just fine.  A nudge when mend is shot and you need a heal is all most healers will need.  I tend to suprise more healers by actually using mend than anything else.  I get a lot of &quot;wow, someone who actually uses mend?&quot;  I have a macro that I hit a few seconds before hitting mend &quot;/g MENDING!  6 minutes until the next mend!&quot;  The reason I hit it a few seconds ahead is to give the caster a chance to duck out of the spell and save the mana.  All are very appreciative of that. <p>----------------------------<br>
